Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Pick and finely chop fronds from @Dill{1/4%oz}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until lightly browned and tender, ~{20%minutes} to ~{25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3%minutes} to ~{5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and set aside to rest.

While chicken cooks, toss @green beans{6%oz} on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of vegetable oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Roast on middle rack until tender, ~{10%minutes} to ~{12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in pan used for chicken, combine @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}; bring to a simmer over medium-high heat, ~{1%minute} to ~{2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and whisk in @sour cream{4%tbsp}, half the chopped dill, and @Dijon mustard{2%tsp} to taste. Turn off heat.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and any resting juices from chicken. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Use 2 TBSP butter and 1/3 cup water for 4 servings.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Drizzle sauce over everything. Garnish with as much remaining chopped dill as you like and serve.